{"id": "EUVD-2025-11166", "enisaUuid": "2d298912-bce3-35be-a92a-2a8f2f4c5146", "description": "In the Linux kernel, the following vulnerability has been resolved:\n\nALSA: timer: Don't take register_mutex with copy_from/to_user()\n\nThe infamous mmap_lock taken in copy_from/to_user() can be often\nproblematic when it's called inside another mutex, as they might lead\nto deadlocks.\n\nIn the case of ALSA timer code, the bad pattern is with\nguard(mutex)(&register_mutex) that covers copy_from/to_user() -- which\nwas mistakenly introduced at converting to guard(), and it had been\ncarefully worked around in the past.\n\nThis patch fixes those pieces simply by moving copy_from/to_user() out\nof the register mutex lock again.", "datePublished": "2025-04-16T14:13:15", "dateUpdated": "2025-10-01T16:15:15", "baseScore": 5.5, "baseScoreVersion": "3.1", "baseScoreVector": "CVSS:3.1/AV:L/AC:L/PR:L/UI:N/S:U/C:N/I:N/A:H", "references": ["https://nvd.nist.gov/vuln/detail/CVE-2025-23134", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/15291b561d8cc835a2eea76b394070cf8e072771", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/296f7a9e15aab276db11206cbc1e2ae1215d7862", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/3424c8f53bc63c87712a7fc22dc13d0cc85fb0d6", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/b074f47e55df93832bbbca1b524c501e6fea1c0d"], "aliases": ["CVE-2025-23134", "GHSA-gxg5-6xg7-gc7q"], "assigner": "Linux", "epss": 0.01, "enisaIdProduct": [{"id": "3a8dc415-701e-3842-9531-0f147d5358e4", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 0"}, {"id": "40bad5c9-7d71-33fb-8262-2ae9c3379238", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "3923de04c81733b30b8ed667569632272fdfed9a <15291b561d8cc835a2eea76b394070cf8e072771"}, {"id": "523af4ed-08b8-3846-a6f0-b1ab03cd5fab", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 6.14.2"}, {"id": "5f31103e-3162-35d4-9822-b181ce6a8563", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 6.12.23"}, {"id": "9a0ba3fc-d7d8-3bd7-b759-2bc99b0ebfa1", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, 